Shipping open development - Changelog, Roadmap, and Wishlist are live.

:INFO [align:center]
Slatesource in the Open
This is the public development feed for Slatesource - a publishing \
platform that turns GitHub repositories into slates. Every significant \
release, decision, and direction is documented here, in the open.

:INFO
What You'll Find Here
Three pages track how Slatesource is built in public.

- Changelog captures releases and improvements, almost per commit.
- Roadmap shows what is planned and in what order.
- Wishlist holds the ideas that are on the radar but not yet committed to.

:NOTE
This slate is maintained as code in the Slatesource GitHub repository \
and syncs automatically on every push. No editorial lag, no curated \
spin. Just the project as it actually is.

